Class RecordValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.stratosphere.types.StringValue
      • org.kepler.stratosphere.type.RecordValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    eu.stratosphere.core.io.IOReadableWritable, eu.stratosphere.types.CopyableValue<eu.stratosphere.types.StringValue>, eu.stratosphere.types.Key, eu.stratosphere.types.NormalizableKey, eu.stratosphere.types.Value, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Appendable, java.lang.CharSequence, java.lang.Comparable<eu.stratosphere.types.Key>

    public class RecordValue
extends eu.stratosphere.types.StringValue
    A PACT Value for Ptolemy record tokens. Record tokens are serialized as strings, so this class inherits all methods from StringValue. This class is necessary to differentiate strings and records.
    Author:
    Daniel Crawl
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
